#New data frame with PValues Adjusted
DF_2 =mutate(data_frame_master,
             PValues_adjusted=p.adjust((data_frame_master$table.PValue),method="BH"))

Including Plots

You can also embed plots, for example:

library(devtools)
## Warning: package 'devtools' was built under R version 3.5.2
## Warning: package 'usethis' was built under R version 3.5.2
library(ggplot2)
## Warning: package 'ggplot2' was built under R version 3.5.2
##Histogram graph
library(ggplot2)
     hist(DF_2$PValues_adjusted, freq =T,breaks=seq(from=0,to=1,by=0.02) ,
     main="Histogram for Adjusted p-vlaues by Benjamini-Hochberg method."
     ,xlab = "Adjusted PValues",las=1
     )
abline(v=0.05,h=0,col="red",lwd=2)
text(0.15, 600, "cutoff", pos=2, col = "blue") 

hist(DF_2$table.PValue, freq =T,breaks=seq(from=0,to=1,by=0.04) ,
     main="Histogram for Unadjusted p-vlaues."
     ,xlab = "PValues",las=1
)
abline(v=0.05,h=0,col="red",lwd=2)
text(0.15, 1000, "cutoff", pos=2, col = "blue") 

 #PCA Analysis
#data preparation
data_PCA=data.frame(DF_2$cpms.Control_Rep1,DF_2$cpms.Control_Rep2,
                    DF_2$cpms.Control_Rep3,DF_2$cpms.Treatment_Rep1,DF_2$cpms.Treatment_Rep2,
                    DF_2$cpms.Treatment_Rep3)
rownames(data_PCA)=paste(DF_2$genes.gene_id)
pca=prcomp(t(data_PCA),center=T, scale. = T)
## make a scree plot
pca.var <- pca$sdev^2
pca.var.per <- round(pca.var/sum(pca.var)*100, 1)
#to show how much variation in the original data each PC accounts for
barplot(pca.var.per, main="Scree Plot", xlab="Principal Component", 
        ylab="Percent Variation")

#GGPlot implementation
#format of data for ggplot
pca.data <- data.frame(Sample=rownames(pca$x),
                       X=pca$x[,1],
                       Y=pca$x[,2])
pca.data
##                                            Sample          X          Y
## DF_2.cpms.Control_Rep1     DF_2.cpms.Control_Rep1  -4.732807  70.304113
## DF_2.cpms.Control_Rep2     DF_2.cpms.Control_Rep2 -54.080088   7.756488
## DF_2.cpms.Control_Rep3     DF_2.cpms.Control_Rep3 -28.575467  25.282187
## DF_2.cpms.Treatment_Rep1 DF_2.cpms.Treatment_Rep1 121.638924  -3.229295
## DF_2.cpms.Treatment_Rep2 DF_2.cpms.Treatment_Rep2  57.067727 -49.025693
## DF_2.cpms.Treatment_Rep3 DF_2.cpms.Treatment_Rep3 -91.318289 -51.087800
#plotting it
ggplot(data=pca.data, aes(x=pca.data$X, y=pca.data$Y, label=pca.data$Sample)) +
  geom_text() +
  xlab(paste("PC1 - ", pca.var.per[1], "%", sep="")) +
  ylab(paste("PC2 - ", pca.var.per[2], "%", sep="")) +
  theme_bw() +
  ggtitle("My PCA Graph")

## get the name of the top 10&100 measurements (genes) that contribute
## most to pc1.
loading_scores = pca$rotation[,1]
gene_scores = abs(loading_scores) ## get the magnitudes
gene_score_ranked = sort(gene_scores, decreasing=TRUE)
top_10_genes = names(gene_score_ranked[1:10])
top_100_genes = names(gene_score_ranked[1:100])

#heatmap
#extracting data for top 100 ranked genes
data_heat_map=data_PCA[rownames(data_PCA) %in% top_100_genes,]
#plotting graph
ggplot(data=data_heat_map, 
       aes( gene_score_ranked[1:100],rownames(data_heat_map)))+
   ylab(paste("Top 100 genes ")) +
  geom_tile(aes(fill = data_heat_map$DF_2.cpms.Control_Rep1, color = "white"))+
  xlab(paste("PC1 - Ranked Values")) +
  ggtitle("TOP 100 Significant Genes based on PC1")

#barplot
#extracting the dataset for top 10 genes
data_bar_plot=data_PCA[rownames(data_PCA) %in% top_10_genes,]
#plotting graph
ggplot(data=data_bar_plot, 
       aes( x=rownames(data_bar_plot), y=gene_score_ranked[1:10]))+
 geom_bar(stat = "identity")+
   xlab(paste("Top 10 genes ")) +
  ylab(paste("PC1 - Ranked Values")) +theme_minimal()+
   ggtitle("TOP 10 Significant Genes based on PC1")

#Volcano PLot
gene_list=DF_2[,c(1,9,10)]
 gene_list$threshold = as.factor(abs(gene_list$table.logFC) > 2
                                 & gene_list$table.PValue < 0.05/length(gene_list$genes.gene_id))
 
ggplot(data=gene_list, aes(x=gene_list$table.logFC, 
                           y=-log10(gene_list$table.PValue)
                           ,colour=gene_list$threshold)) + 
  geom_point(alpha=0.4, size=1.75) +
  
  xlim(c(-10, 10)) + ylim(c(0, 15)) +
  xlab("log2 fold change") + ylab("-log10 p-value")+
  ggtitle("Volcano Plot")

Note that the echo = FALSE parameter was added to the code chunk to prevent printing of the R code that generated the plot.
